{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17492959","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17492959"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T06:51:13+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T06:51:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1192"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1192","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1192"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.23,0.63,0.04,0.09,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1192"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70966"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1192","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1192"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1192"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56435"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"136"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"1052"},{"type":"tags","id":"3382"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7074"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7094"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23173"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42243"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44504"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70966","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70966"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with a one-day history of increasing upper abdominal pain, nausea and vomiting. He has never had these symptoms before. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. He is a non-smoker and drinks two standard drinks per day, but reports excessive alcohol consumption the night before his symptoms started.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears unwell. His pulse rate is 100/min, blood pressure 110/65 mmHg, respiratory rate 18/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 37.2\u00b0C. There is tenderness across the upper abdomen without evidence of peritonitis. His serum lipase is 520 U/L (0-160).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Nasogastric insertion and nil-by-mouth","Intravenous fluid resuscitation","Total parenteral nutrition","Oral nutrition as tolerated","Nasojejunal feeds"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has acute pancreatitis, likely alcohol-induced. While the clinical findings suggest a relatively mild episode, early fluid resuscitation is crucial in preventing complications. \u003Cstrong\u003EIntravenous fluid resuscitation\u003C/strong\u003E should be initiated promptly to maintain adequate organ perfusion and prevent third-spacing of fluids. The rate should be titrated based on clinical response, urine output, and haemodynamic parameters.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENasogastric insertion and nil-by-mouth\u003C/strong\u003E is no longer routinely recommended in mild pancreatitis. Traditional practice of bowel rest has not been shown to improve outcomes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETotal parenteral nutrition\u003C/strong\u003E is reserved for severe cases where enteral nutrition is not possible for prolonged periods. It carries risks of line infection and metabolic complications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral nutrition\u003C/strong\u003E should be commenced as soon as pain and nausea allow, typically within 24-48 hours. Early oral feeding has been shown to reduce length of stay and complications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENasojejunal feeds\u003C/strong\u003E may be considered in severe pancreatitis where oral intake is not tolerated, but are not indicated in mild cases such as this.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe severity of pancreatitis cannot be determined by lipase levels alone. Other factors such as organ dysfunction, SIRS criteria, and various scoring systems (e.g., APACHE II, Ranson\u0027s criteria, Atlanta classification) should be considered in determining severity and prognosis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Early fluid resuscitation is the cornerstone of initial management in acute pancreatitis.","The severity of pancreatitis cannot be determined by lipase levels alone.","Oral intake should be commenced as soon as pain and nausea allow."],"references":["de-Madaria E, Buxbaum JL, Maisonneuve P, et al. Aggressive or Moderate Fluid Resuscitation\nin Acute Pancreatitis. N Engl J Med 2022;387:989-1000. Available at: https://www.nejm.org/doi/full/10.1056/NEJMoa2202884","Yaowmaneerat T, Sirinawasatien A. Update on the strategy for intravenous fluid treatment in acute pancreatitis. World J Gastrointest Pharmacol Ther. 2023;14(3):22-32. https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37179816/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56435"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1192"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"17353"},{"type":"media","id":"17354"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"17353","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/17353"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/7b70d023-1726-4b10-ad1a-16d6126d6cf5.jpg","thumbUr